    "The data extraction form was first completed by one reviewer (Y.Y.",
    "), and subsequently verified by another reviewer (A.P.)",
    "for correctness, with any discrepancies resolved through discussion.",
    "The quality of each included study was assessed through the 2022 journal impact factor (not applicable for proceedings of conferences, workshops, or symposiums), the h5-index of the publication (journal, conference, workshop, or symposium) from Google Scholar, and the number of citations listed in Web of Science as of November 13, 2024.",
    "The h-index is an author-level metric that measures both the productivity and citation impact of a publication, and the h5-index is the h-index for articles published in the last 5 complete years (2018-2022)."
